You are the youngest son of the 1st of us and the 2nd. You are the brother of the 2nd. Out of my love and affection for you, and in return for my love, I wish to give you some immovable property, and I hereby transfer the immovable property as per the schedule below, which has been our ancestral property and has been our full rightful owner till today, to you free of charge and transfer the deed to you on this very day. From this date, you will have full rights to the deed and you and your children and grandchildren will have the right to sell it freely, paying the taxes of the Sri Panchayat yourself. In this regard, we will resolve any and all disputes arising from any cause whatsoever, at our own expense, and will deliver the Scheduled Property to you without any hindrance. We hereby give you this deed of transfer of the Scheduled Property to you on this day, and we hereby give you this deed of transfer, stating that we have not subjected the said Property to any other encumbrances and that the said Property is an undisputed Property in all respects. We are liable to pay the depreciation tax on any missionaries, quarries, or other establishments found to exist in the land transferred by this deed.
